# 📍 Day 12 — Containers in AWS

## 🎯 Objective

Understand container-based application deployment in AWS.

---

## 🐳 What are Containers?

* Lightweight application packaging
* Include code + dependencies
* Portable across environments

---

## ⚙️ ECS (Elastic Container Service)

### 📌 Key Features

* AWS-managed container orchestration
* Simpler than Kubernetes
* Integrates with AWS services

---

## 🚀 EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service)

### 📌 Key Features

* Managed Kubernetes
* Industry standard
* More control, more complexity

---

## 📦 Fargate

### 📌 Key Features

* Serverless container execution
* No infrastructure management
* Works with ECS & EKS

---

## 🗂️ ECR (Elastic Container Registry)

### 📌 Key Features

* Stores Docker images
* Secure & scalable

---

## ⚖️ Comparison

| Service | Use Case                       |
| ------- | ------------------------------ |
| ECS     | Simple container orchestration |
| EKS     | Kubernetes-based control       |
| Fargate | Serverless containers          |
| ECR     | Image storage                  |

---

## 💡 Key Learnings

* Containers improve portability
* ECS is simpler, EKS is more powerful
* Fargate removes infrastructure management

---

## 🚧 Challenges Faced

* Understanding ECS vs EKS difference
* When to use Fargate vs EC2

